parameters:
What lies ahead is the [Training Grounds]. If you feel
uneasy about heading into enemy territory, it would be good
to fight here and improve your skills.

In the previous battle with the demons, almost all of the
Iga ninjas were killed. My brother also... he's not coming
back. Please, fight alongside us.

It seems that women need a letter of introduction to enter
the pleasure district. It would be good to ask someone you
know might have one.

It's like not seeing what's right under your nose that the
Yotsuya haunted mansion has become a den for little
demons... It's not like I didn't investigate because I was
scared of ghosts, okay?

...Demons are my sworn enemies. I am determined to fight
until they are annihilated.

Yugiri-dono should have gone to Suranashi Village... Huh,
why is Karin-dono here?

Yugiri-sama is resting in the futon. We are doing our best
to ensure her injuries heal quickly, so please be at ease.
Also, it seems a new shipping route has been established at
Uraga. If you pay the fare, I believe you can travel from
Uraga to Mujou Island.

The wounds I sustained at the bandit fortress have fully
healed. From now on, when we travel far, I can fight
alongside you.

Yugiri-sama is not at home. She hasn't returned here, you
know?

The enemy is Fuma... There's no way the ninjas of this era
can lose to those from the Sengoku period. If you're going
to settle this, I'll fight alongside you.

The townspeople are in a state of panic since Edo Castle
burned down. Peace will not come to this world unless we
defeat the chief of the demons. We must win at all costs,
Karin--

Who would have thought that the master thief Mouse Komachi
would fight alongside us. I'm well aware of your exploits.
It's truly reassuring. Please help Yugiri-dono.

The bandits captured at the bandit fortress were reportedly
exiled to an island. This should improve the public order in
Sunudashi Village somewhat.

It seems you've heard the story. Once we, the Iga ninjas,
numbered 50, but now only about 10 remain. The enemy is a
demon--we need to reinforce our strength.

It was careless of me to not consider the presence of a
demon in the haunted mansion. I express my respect for your
brave decoy investigation.

I wish Yugiri-dono would act more like a leader, but she
always ends up on the front lines... It's quite troubling. I
do wish she would rest a bit.
... (So this eerie building was a ninja mansion...)
Karin, you've arrived. I've been waiting for you.

Wow... I never knew a real ninja mansion existed. And right
in the middle of Marunouchi...

Just to confirm, by coming to this mansion, you mean to say
that you'll fight alongside us, correct?

Yes. As the kunoichi Karin, I will fight with you all. If
that means all my past deeds will be pardoned, then it's a
small price to pay.

Thank you. With Karin-dono, who was once known as Mouse
Komachi, joining us, the morale of our Iga ninja group will
surely rise.
Nice to meet you, everyone from the Iga ninjas

The Iga ninja group has a long history and has existed since
ancient times to protect Edo. It is an organization directly
under the shogunate. We handle crimes like arson and theft
publicly through the magistrate's office, and any other
adversaries are secretly eliminated by our covert operations
team.

So the adversaries are demons... It's hard to believe at
first.

You can say that because you haven't seen a demon yet.
There's no falsehood in what Lord Shinana has stated. Edo is
being targeted by demons.

I heard about it from the town crier before coming here.
Lately, courtesans have been going missing one after another
--could it be that...

You catch on quickly. It is indeed the work of demons. Night
after night, lesser demons appear and abduct courtesans to
somewhere.
...Do we know where they're being taken?

The lesser demons are swift, and they manage to lose us
during pursuit. That's why we need your help, Karin.

I see. Then it's best if I pretend to be a courtesan and let
myself be abducted to discover the demons' lair.

--! What did you say, Karin? You intend to become a
courtesan yourself and conduct an undercover investigation
against the demons?

Yes. It's unbearable to see more courtesans become victims.
If it comes down to it, I'm confident I can escape if they
try to kill me.

Very well. If you're prepared to be bait, then take this
with you. You should appear as a courtesan to those around
you.

Receiving a mat and all, it's getting quite serious, but I
just have to pretend to be a courtesan, right...?

Yes. Once night falls, search thoroughly throughout Edo. I'm
counting on you, Karin.

Alright. If a lesser demon shows up, I'll count on you for
backup and pursuit, Yugiri-chan--

! Hey, Karin! Stop with the 'chan'! My subordinates will
start taking me lightly!

Ahaha! It's fine. I've decided to call you Yugiri-chan from
now on. Feel free to call me Karin-chan too

I'm going home for today. I'll start the investigation
tomorrow.

...Just a word of caution, make sure you only pretend to be
a courtesan. If any men approach you, turn them away.
Understood?
\c[17][Note: From Now On, Clicking On The Lantern Next To Your Home Will Turn It To Night.]\c[0]

From Now On, Clicking On The Lantern Next To Your Home Will
Turn It To Night.]: From Now On, Clicking On The Lantern
Next To Your Home Will Turn It To Night.]

I see. Then speak to me again once you've made up your mind.
It's understandable to have reservations about fighting
grotesque demons.

Even if I'm told to stay in bed, my body will grow weak...
I'm sorry I can't fight alongside you, Karin. That war demon
who uses flames is a formidable enemy. Don't lose.
